INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
SELECT m.id, 'Overtime', 'overtime', '<h2>Overtime</h2>
<p>Overtime pay only pays for overtime of actual work hours over 40 hours. In other words, Annual Time cannot be used to be paid for overtime or to "make" 40 hrs. on a time card for the week.</p>
<blockquote><p><strong>Holiday pay is treated as regular work hours in reference to determining OT pay.</strong></p></blockquote>
<p>In the event the company closes for any weather related or any reason outside of IAT control, the day(s) closed will not be compensated with regular pay. You have the option of working on Friday to make up the time or you may use your annual time for compensation. If annual time is used it will not count towards OT.</p>', 35, TRUE, 2
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO learn_lessons (module_id, title, slug, content, display_order, is_published, estimated_minutes)
SELECT m.id, 'Sick Time', 'sick-time', '<h2>Sick Time</h2>
<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: "Everything hurts and I''m dying" Parks and Recreation meme — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>
<p>Sick Time is the paid time off you get if you''re feeling under the weather or dealing with an injury that keeps you from working. It''s also there for you if you need to see the doctor, dentist, or eye doctor, or if someone in your family needs your care.</p>
<p>It''s not like a free pass to take time off whenever you feel like it. Think of it more as a special privilege that''s there when you really need it, not something to be taken advantage of. If someone starts going overboard with taking sick days or not following the rules, there might be some consequences.</p>
<blockquote><p><strong>Permanent full-time employees will earn 80 hours per year (1.54 hours per week) for Sick Time to be taken as paid time off.</strong></p></blockquote>
<figure class="img-missing"><figcaption>📷 Image from Trainual: Sick Time Policy Intro video thumbnail — re-upload via admin editor</figcaption></figure>
<p>Extra or temporary employees are not eligible for sick time.</p>
<h3>Sick Time shall be granted to eligible employees for the following reasons:</h3>
<ul>
<li>Personal illness or injury</li>
<li>Illness of an employee''s spouse, parent, child</li>
<li>Medical, dental or optical appointment</li>
<li>After bereavement leave (refer to section 5.6) has been used for the death of an employee''s spouse, mother, father, brother, sister, child, grandparents, grandchild</li>
<li>Aside from the reasons above, Sick Time may be used for Annual Shutdown</li>
</ul>
<p>If you''re feeling under the weather or can''t make it to work for any reason listed above, make sure to give your supervisor a shout. Call them or drop a message before your day starts. And if you''re out for more than a day, keep them in the loop about how you''re doing, unless they tell you not to bother.</p>
<p>If you don''t keep your supervisor updated, you might not get paid sick leave for the time you''re off. If you''re out for more than 3 days, we''ll need a note from your doctor or if you''ve got any doctor''s appointments planned.</p>
<blockquote><p><strong>FUN FACT: Sick time carries over.</strong></p>
<p>Don''t worry about not using all your sick hours; they''ll carry over to next year. You can accumulate up to 160 hours. If you find yourself with more than that at the end of the year, we''ll pay out the extra. But remember, if you''ve used up all your sick time, you''ll have to dip into your annual leave.</p></blockquote>
<blockquote><p><em>Just so we''re clear, sick time can''t be swapped for vacation time.</em></p></blockquote>
<p><strong>REMEMBER!</strong> Before you head back to work, make sure you''ve been fever-free for at least 24 hours. Your manager has the final say on approving your sick leave.</p>', 36, TRUE, 3
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'company' AND m.slug = 'company-policies'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
