SELECT m.id, 'IP Addressing of Controllers and HMI', 'ip-addressing-controllers-hmi', '<h2>IP Addressing of Controllers and HMI</h2><h3>Standard IP Address Configuration for IAT Systems</h3><p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> May 1<br><strong>Applies To:</strong> All outgoing systems unless a customer-specific configuration is provided</p><h3>Overview</h3><p>To support future remote access capabilities and ensure consistency across all deployed systems, a standardized IP addressing structure will be implemented for all PLCs and HMIs.</p><h3>Required Configuration</h3><p><strong>PLC</strong></p><ul><li>IP Address: <code>192.168.1.4</code></li><li>Subnet Mask: <code>255.255.255.0</code></li><li>Gateway: <code>192.168.1.1</code></li></ul><p><strong>HMI</strong></p><ul><li>IP Address: <code>192.168.1.15</code></li><li>Subnet Mask: <code>255.255.255.0</code></li><li>Gateway: <code>192.168.1.1</code></li></ul><h3>Key Notes</h3><ul><li>The specific IP address is less critical than maintaining a consistent structure.</li><li>The <code>.1</code> address in a subnet is typically reserved for the gateway, which aligns with standard networking practices.</li><li>Subnet mask and gateway configuration are essential components of proper network setup and must be included to prevent future field issues.</li><li>Modems shipped with systems should also follow this addressing structure, with the gateway set to <code>.1</code>.</li></ul><h3>Implementation Requirement</h3><ul><li>Apply this configuration to all applicable systems starting May 1.</li><li>Include a label with the IP configuration on the inside of the unit door for reference in the field.</li></ul><h3>Exceptions</h3><ul><li>If a customer provides a specific IP scheme, follow their requirements instead of this standard.</li></ul><p><em>Provided by Peter Furey</em></p>', 18, TRUE, 3
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'technical-training' AND m.slug = 'engineering'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
