SELECT m.id, 'PXR3 Controller Setup for SCR Heater Modulation (4–20 mA Control)', 'pxr3-controller-setup-scr-heater', '<h2>PXR3 Controller Setup for SCR Heater Modulation (4–20 mA Control)</h2><h3>Purpose</h3><p>This process outlines how to configure a Fuji PXR3 controller to:</p><ul><li>accept a <strong>4–20 mA</strong> temperature input from a signal conditioner</li><li>provide a <strong>4–20 mA</strong> output to an SCR</li><li>modulate heater output based on process temperature</li></ul><p><strong>Reference controller:</strong> PXR3-BEY2-5V0A1<br><strong>Reference project:</strong> 4440</p><h3>Overview</h3><p>In this setup, a Type J thermocouple sends temperature feedback to a TX rail signal conditioner, which converts the thermocouple signal into a 4–20 mA input for the PXR3. The PXR3 then uses that input to control heater output and sends a 4–20 mA output signal to the SCR for heater modulation.</p><h3>Required Components</h3><ul><li>Fuji PXR3 controller</li><li>Type J thermocouple</li><li>TX rail signal conditioner</li><li>SCR accepting 4–20 mA control input</li></ul><h3>Input Configuration (Temperature Signal)</h3><h3>1. Configure the input type</h3><p>Set the controller input to accept <strong>4–20 mA</strong>.</p><p>Parameter: <code>P-N2 = 16</code> &rarr; 4–20 mA input</p><h3>2. Set scaling in engineering units</h3><p>Set the temperature range to match the application.</p><p>Parameters:</p><ul><li><code>P-SL = -100°F</code> &rarr; lower limit</li><li><code>P-SU = 760°F</code> &rarr; upper limit</li></ul><p>These values scale the 4–20 mA signal to the desired operating temperature range.</p><h3>PID Tuning</h3><h3>3. Enable Auto-Tune</h3><p>Use Auto-Tune to let the controller determine the correct PID values for the system.</p><p>Parameter: <code>AT = 1</code></p><p><strong>What happens during Auto-Tune:</strong></p><ul><li>The controller will cycle the heaters <strong>on and off twice</strong></li><li>It will calculate the appropriate PID values automatically</li><li>When complete, the controller will run using the tuned PID loop</li></ul><h3>Output Configuration (SCR Control)</h3><h3>4. View or confirm the 4–20 mA output</h3><p>To display or verify analog output:</p><p>Parameters:</p><ul><li><code>dSP = 127</code></li><li><code>Ao-L = 2</code> &rarr; enables analog output display</li></ul><p>This allows confirmation that the controller is sending the expected analog output signal to the SCR.</p><h3>Best Practices</h3><p><strong>Verify TX rail scaling before tuning</strong><br>Make sure the signal conditioner is scaled correctly before starting Auto-Tune.<br><em>Why it matters:</em> Incorrect scaling will cause inaccurate temperature feedback and poor PID performance.</p><p><strong>Confirm thermocouple polarity</strong><br>Before conditioning the signal, verify the <strong>Type J thermocouple polarity</strong> is correct.<br><em>Why it matters:</em> Incorrect polarity will result in false temperature readings.</p><p><strong>Do not disturb the system during Auto-Tune</strong><br>Allow the system to complete Auto-Tune without interference.<br><em>Why it matters:</em> Stable operating conditions are necessary for accurate PID calculation.</p><p><strong>Confirm SCR input range</strong><br>Verify the SCR is configured to accept the same <strong>4–20 mA signal range</strong> being sent by the PXR3.<br><em>Why it matters:</em> A mismatch can cause improper heater modulation.</p><h3>Important Note on Units</h3><p>Units do <strong>not</strong> need to be explicitly set in the controller because the PXR3 is reading a <strong>4–20 mA signal</strong>, not a direct thermocouple input. As long as the <strong>upper and lower scaling limits</strong> are set correctly, the controller will interpret the signal properly.</p><h3>Parameter Summary</h3><table><tr><th>Function</th><th>Parameter</th><th>Setting</th></tr><tr><td>Input type</td><td>P-N2</td><td>16</td></tr><tr><td>Lower scale limit</td><td>P-SL</td><td>-100°F</td></tr><tr><td>Upper scale limit</td><td>P-SU</td><td>760°F</td></tr><tr><td>Enable Auto-Tune</td><td>AT</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>Display setting</td><td>dSP</td><td>127</td></tr><tr><td>Analog output display</td><td>Ao-L</td><td>2</td></tr></table><h3>Expected Result</h3><p>Once setup is complete:</p><ul><li>the PXR3 reads the conditioned 4–20 mA temperature signal</li><li>the input is scaled to the correct temperature range</li><li>Auto-Tune sets PID values automatically</li><li>the controller sends a 4–20 mA output to the SCR</li><li>heater modulation follows process demand accurately</li></ul>', 70, TRUE, 5
FROM learn_modules m JOIN learn_categories c ON c.id = m.category_id
WHERE c.slug = 'technical-training' AND m.slug = 'engineering'
ON CONFLICT (module_id, slug) DO NOTHING;
